Creating images with R

with a little bit of magick

Jordan Lazarus

2023-03-13

My meme

This is a football meme about the football club Chelsea F.C. not qualifying for the Champions League nor the Europa League, but the Conference League, and the manager of Chelsea F.C. being happy about qualifying for the Conference League despite the Champions League being the biggest tournament in club football and Europa League being second to the Champions League (Conference League being third to the Champions League. Chelsea F.C. are currently 10th place in the Premier League out of 20 teams despite finishing last season in 3rd. I have found and put together these images to create this meme.

library(magick)

#Champions League Image
champions_league <- image_read("https://www.footballempires.spinningworldinc.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/graham-potter-manager-chelsea-looks-798779632.jpg") %>%
  image_scale(400)

#Europa League Image
europa_league <- image_read("https://th.bing.com/th/id/OIF.pJTchuHE8vsoMDOrOO9Wzw?pid=ImgDet&rs=1") %>%
  image_scale(400)

#Conference League Image
conference_league <- image_read("https://th.bing.com/th/id/OIF.PI9qC89SqYXt9m8l6nnoUw?w=250&h=180&c=7&r=0&o=5&dpr=1.5&pid=1.7") %>%
  image_scale(400)

champions_text <- image_blank(width = 400, 
                          height = 266, 
                          color = "#000000") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "Champions\nLeague",
                 color = "#FFFFFF",
                 size = 80,
                 font = "Impact",
                 gravity = "center")

europa_text <- image_blank(width = 400, 
                         height = 224, 
                         color = "#000000") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "Europa\nLeague",
                 color = "#FFFFFF",
                 size = 80,
                 font = "Impact",
                 gravity = "center")

conference_text <- image_blank(width = 400, 
                       height = 288, 
                       color = "#000000") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "Conference\nLeague",
                 color = "#FFFFFF",
                 size = 80,
                 font = "Impact",
                 gravity = "center")

first_row <- c(champions_league, champions_text) %>%
  image_append()

second_row <- c(europa_league, europa_text) %>%
  image_append()

third_row <- c(conference_league, conference_text) %>%
  image_append()

meme <- c(first_row, second_row, third_row) %>%
  image_append(stack = TRUE)

meme %>% image_write("STATS220_meme.png")

meme

My animation

This meme is about the footballer Luis Suarez biting a player on the opposing team and getting a 10 match suspension. These images were put together to create this animation.

library(magick)

# reading the images
suarez_bite1 <- image_read("https://th.bing.com/th/id/OIP.N2b4uSq6mDNE-McFrM9aOAEPDm?pid=ImgDet&rs=1") %>%
  image_scale(400)

suarez_bite2 <- image_read("https://i2-prod.mirror.co.uk/incoming/article1846056.ece/ALTERNATES/s1200/Suarez-bites-Ivanovic.jpg") %>%
  image_scale(400)

suarez_bite3 <- image_read("https://th.bing.com/th/id/R.334d896fd358f9d4b85f7fbc102f1a8f?rik=65O6xa6kTZjLVg&riu=http%3a%2f%2fwww.totalprosports.com%2fwp-content%2fuploads%2f2013%2f04%2fluis-suarez-bite-ivanovic-595x409.jpg&ehk=7owc4i%2bK2aa%2fP4iaA6QCvr147oXsDBoZY52PsapeQEw%3d&risl=&pid=ImgRaw&r=0") %>%
  image_scale(400)

suarez_bite4 <- image_read("https://th.bing.com/th/id/R.3e1bb21cf5f23e7e5f0546cc1ea9346f?rik=xz%2famBysOmjAdw&riu=http%3a%2f%2fd.ibtimes.co.uk%2fen%2ffull%2f364281%2fluis-suarez-mountings.jpg&ehk=EFWoWSzBg3UwBp1CmhXBYTq0cazDeYm%2fGstCKqoWlP8%3d&risl=&pid=ImgRaw&r=0") %>%
  image_scale(400)

# creating the frames of the GIF
frame1 <- suarez_bite1 %>%
  image_scale(400) %>%
  image_extent("500x500", gravity = "center")

frame2 <- suarez_bite2 %>%
  image_scale(400) %>%
  image_extent("500x500", gravity = "center")

frame3 <- suarez_bite3 %>%
  image_scale(400) %>%
  image_extent("500x500", gravity = "center")

frame4 <- suarez_bite4 %>%
  image_scale(400) %>%
  image_extent("500x500", gravity = "center")

# putting the frames in order using a vector
animation <- c(frame1, frame2, frame3, frame4)

# creating an animation
stats_animation <- image_animate(animation, fps = 1)

stats_animation %>% image_write("STATS220_animation.gif")
